\begin{abstract}
    Let $G$ be a finite group and ${\mathsf{cd}}(G)$ denote the set of complex irreducible character degrees of $G$. In this paper, we prove that if $G$ is a finite group and $H$ is an almost simple group whose socle is a sporadic simple group such that ${\mathsf{cd}}(G) ={\mathsf{cd}}(H)$, then there exists an abelian subgroup $A$ of $G$ such that $G/A$ is isomorphic to $H$. This study is heading towards the study of an extension of Huppert's conjecture (2000) for almost simple groups.
\end{abstract}

